The body of a suspected male vagrant was discovered by the passerby at around 12:00, under the bridge on the corner of DR Mandela Drive- and John Magagula Street. According to information gathered at the scene, the man was still seen walking along the street early in the morning. By the time of the discovery, rigor mortis had already set in and it is suspected that the man had been dead for several hours. Though the cause of death has not yet been determined, an inquest has been opened by the police.